[28.5, "o", "Analyzing request: \"Explain how a hash map works\"\r\n"]
[28.8, "o", "Mode: thinking | No code execution needed\r\n"]
[29.3, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;35mрџ§  THINKER\u001b[0m \u001b[2m(openai / gpt-4o)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[29.6, "o", "A hash map (also called hash table or dictionary) is a data structure\r\n"]
[29.9, "o", "that stores key-value pairs with O(1) average-case lookup time.\r\n"]
[30.2, "o", "\r\n"]
[30.4, "o", "**How it works:**\r\n"]
[30.7, "o", "1. A hash function converts the key into an integer (hash code)\r\n"]
[31.0, "o", "2. The hash code is mapped to an array index: `index = hash(key) % array_size`\r\n"]
[31.3, "o", "3. The value is stored at that index in the underlying array\r\n"]
[31.6, "o", "\r\n"]
[31.8, "o", "**Collision handling:**\r\n"]
[32.1, "o", "- Chaining: each bucket holds a linked list of entries\r\n"]
[32.4, "o", "- Open addressing: probe for the next empty slot\r\n"]
[32.8, "o", "\r\n"]
